metadata.name: Youth
metadata.description:
10 years ago, I learned a lot about head anatomy, mechanics, languages, zoology, even poetry. But none of them I finished, the only thing that finished was the answer of ''what do I really like?" Well, I like the beauty of brain structure, the complexity of machines, the uniqueness of language and the feeling of poetry. Since then I started collecting beautiful pictures, complex, structured things and feelings into 1 picture without knowing that technique was called Collage.

And what you see now is the contents of my head when I was young which I poured into a collage that was made on January 9th and finished on January 14th.


This collage is 100% handmade. Uses 7 editions of NatGeo and 1 sheet from Westminster Abbey book.

Size 25 x 24 cm
